\title{TaxaHabitat: Habitat Assignment and Spatial Quality Control for Taxonomic Occurrences}
\description{
Assigns habitat classifications to taxonomic occurrence records using LLM prompts and performs spatial quality control. Receives occurrence data from TaxaFetch and produces habitat-annotated, spatially screened records for input to TaxaExpect. Part of the TaxaID ecosystem.

Assigns habitat classifications to species using LLM-based biological
consensus and performs spatial quality control on occurrence records.
Supports multiple habitat schemes (3-category, IUCN Level 1, custom).
